{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d931da1a-379c-462b-a91c-a928f34305c4","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName);\n}\n```\n\n**Why switch:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`)\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and lets you inspect the exception (message, `ParamName`, inner exception, etc.)\n- The test fails immediately with a clear message if no exception is thrown","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"38a1e3fd-6662-4dbf-b06f-97b1207423f4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":258,"requestId":"67C2:13C959:2B19B8A:2FB89EA:69FD3E22"},"id":"9109be65-c326-4c1f-a6ac-c73e12e2ef0e","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:36:42.565Z","parentId":"28ee308b-9c6e-46e3-ba15-6d1bcdca680c"}
